default2.8
default&#xa0;&#xa0; 
defaultYoung people make significantly fewer car journeys than they did – down from almost 600 trips per person each year in the mid-1990s to 377 trips in 2011 – and fewer young people now own cars or have driving 
defaultlicences (only 38% of 17-20 year olds now have a driving license compared to 48% in the early 1990s)
default.
default The provision of public transport to compensate for this trend has however not been taken into account by local or central governments. 
