default7.1
default&#xa0;&#xa0; 
defaultFunding transport services in isolated communities is getting progressively harder and harder with spending cuts across the boar
defaultd since 2010. 
defaultThere must be a greater focus on transport integration and Local Authorities working together with all transport operators. 
default&#xa0;
default7.2
default&#xa0;&#xa0; 
defaultDifferent modes of 
defaultt
defaultransport should be working together not against each other – it should not be a case of bus versus rail. 
default&#xa0;
default7.3
default&#xa0;&#xa0; 
defaultWhilst many argue for spending cuts to transport across the country
default,
default there must be a 
defaultgeneral
default recognition that investing in passenger transport is goo
defaultd for the country with wider benefits experienced economicall
defaulty, socially and environmentally to having a good transport system. People in isolated communities must not be left behind when budgets are cut and savings are made. 
default&#xa0;
default7.4
default&#xa0;&#xa0; 
defaultA way forward would be to 
defaultcreate a ring fenced fund from Central Government for local buses which would p
defaultool investment in buses from the Government departments that most benefit 
defaultfrom them – DWP, DfE, DH. This would be d
defaultistributed as now through the Bus Service Operators Grant or t
defaulthrough a new approach that supports buses in rural as well as in urban areas based on accessibility.
